      • getChargeState

        public java.lang.Integer getChargeState()
        Returns the current charge state of the saved beacon.

        The returned value is an integer which represents the charge state in percent. This value is greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 100. If the charge state of the beacon could not be determined, it returns Integer.MIN_VALUE (-214748368).

        Returns:
        The current charge state of the saved beacon in percent.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Checks whether two Beacon instances are considerable to be equal.

        Two beacon instances are "equal" in the sense of this method if they share at least the same UUID-Major-Minor combination.

        More formally, two beacons are considered equal if and only if:
        1. The two instances are the same OR
        2. The two instances are of the Beacon class AND all of these attributes of the two Beacon instances are equal:
        - UUID
        - Major
        - Minor.

        Parameters:
        o - As Object to compare to the Beacon instance.
        Returns:
        true if the two instances are "equal", which means they share at least the same UUID-Major-Minor combination, false otherwise.
